        {
            "type": "h2",
            "content": "Forming the <i>Partizip II</i>"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The main verb of the <i>Perfekt</i> tense will take the <i>Partizip II</i> (past participle) form. In English, it is equivalent to forms like \"eaten,\" \"gone,\" or \"written.\""
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "The formation of Partizip II depends on whether the verb is regular (weak), irregular (strong), or a mixed verb (with characteristics of both)."
        },
        {
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Regular verbs"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "We will follow the next steps:"
        },
        {
            "type": "html",
            "content": "<ol><li>Remove the infinitive ending (<b data-verb-prefix>-en</b> or <b data-verb-prefix>-n</b>):<ul><li>mach<s>en</s> <i>(to do)</i> → mach</li></ul></li>   <li>Add the prefix <b data-verb-stem>ge-</b> to the stem:<ul><li>mach → <b data-verb-stem>ge</b>-mach</li></ul><li>Add the suffix \"<b data-verb-prefix>-t</b>\":<ul><li>ge-mach → gemach<b data-verb-prefix>t</b></li><ul></li></ol>"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "So, the Partizip II of \"$__machen-machen[verb-link-hover]__$\" is \"<b data-verb-stem>ge<b>mach<b data-verb-prefix>t</b>.\""
        },
        {
            "type": "html",
            "content": "<p>More examples:</p><ul><li>lernen <i>(to learn)</i> → <b data-verb-stem>ge</b>lern<b data-verb-prefix>t</b></li><li>spielen <i>(to play)</i> → <b data-verb-stem>ge</b>spiel<b data-verb-prefix>t</b></li><ul>"
        },
        {
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Irregular verbs"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "For most of the irregular verbs we will follow the next steps:"
        },
        {
            "type": "html",
            "content": "<ol><li>Change the stem vowel (if necessary, as per the verb's pattern) and remove the infinitive ending (<b data-verb-prefix>-en</b> or <b data-verb-prefix>-n</b>):<ul><li>schreib<s>en</s> <i>(to write)</i> → schr<b data-verb-stem>ie</b>b- (past stem)</li></ul></li>   <li>Add the prefix <b data-verb-stem>ge-</b> to the stem:<ul><li>schrieb → <b data-verb-stem>ge</b>-schrieben</li></ul><li>Add the suffix \"<b data-verb-prefix>-en</b>\":<ul><li>ge-schrieben → geschrieb<b data-verb-prefix>en</b></li><ul></li></ol>"
        },
        {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": "So, the Partizip II of \"$__schreiben-schreiben[verb-link-hover]__$\" is \"<b data-verb-stem>ge<b>schrieb<b data-verb-prefix>en</b>.\""
        },
        {
            "type": "html",
            "content": "<p>More examples:</p><ul><li>sehen <i>(to see)</i>  → <b data-verb-stem>ge</b>seh<b data-verb-prefix>en</b></li><li>sprechen <i>(to speak)</i>  → <b data-verb-stem>ge</b>sproch<b data-verb-prefix>en</b></li><ul>"
        },
        {
            "type": "h3",
            "content": "Special Cases"
        },
        {
            "type": "h4",
            "content": "Verbs with prefixes"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Separable prefixed verbs:</b> <b data-verb-stem>ge-</b> is inserted between the prefix and the stem:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich habe Obst und Gemüse eingekauft",
                            "text": "Example: Ich <b>habe</b> Obst und Gemüse $__ein<b data=verb=stem>ge</b>kauft-einkaufen[verb-link-hover]__$",
                            "translation": "(I have shopped for fruits and vegetables.)"
                        }
                    },
                    {
                        "text": "<b>Inseparable prefixed verbs:</b> there is no <b data-verb-stem>ge-</b> added:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich habe die Aufgabe verstanden.",
                            "text": "Ich <b>habe</b> die Aufgabe $__verstanden-verstehen[verb-link-hover]__$",
                            "translation": "(He went to Berlin)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "h4",
            "content": "Verbs ending with -ieren"
        },
{
            "type": "list",
            "itemsList": {
                "items": [
                    {
                        "text": "Verbs ending with <b>-ieren</b> do not take the </b> <b data-verb-stem>ge-</b> prefix and will take the <b data-verb-prefix>-t</b> ending:",
                        "example": {
                            "audio": "Ich habe an der Universität studiert.",
                            "text": "Example: Ich <b>habe</b> an der Universität $__studier<b data=verb=prefix>t</b>-studieren[verb-link-hover]__$.",
                            "translation": "(I have shopped for fruits and vegetables.)"
                        }
                    }
                ]
            }
        }
    ]
